    "response_text": "The commercial begins on a black screen.\n\nIt then cuts to a sequence of medical/anatomical imagery on a pale background. A male torso is shown with an illustrated heart overlaid on the chest and white arrows pointing toward it. This is followed by a close-up strip of a person’s eyes, then a series of anatomical drawings: pelvis and leg bones, knee joints, rib cage and spine, skull, hand and hip/leg bones, chest and shoulder muscles, facial muscles, and the muscles/tendons of feet. The images resemble textbook anatomy plates, with numbered labels visible on many parts.\n\nAfter the anatomical montage, a small full-body male figure appears centered against a plain light background. He is shirtless and wearing patterned shorts, standing upright on a small dark rectangular base.\n\nThe commercial then shifts to automobile imagery. Close-ups show parts of a car interior: a door control panel with power-window-style switches, then a dashboard audio/control unit with many buttons and a digital display. A wider interior view shows the car seats and steering wheel area, focusing on the seating layout and upholstery.\n\nNext, the exterior/mechanical focus begins. A red car side panel and wheel are shown in close-up, with the wheel appearing to rotate or blur between frames. The commercial then uses technical cutaway-style illustrations of a car, showing the engine bay, front grille, wheel/brake assembly, suspension or drivetrain components, and other internal mechanical systems. One front plate area reads “LEGACY.” A wider cutaway drawing shows the whole car with its internal components visible, including the cabin, engine area, wheels, and drivetrain layout.\n\nNear the end, there is an orange-toned blurred transition or abstract close-up; the content is not clearly identifiable from the sampled frame.\n\nThe final frame is a plain light end card with black italic text. It reads: “Subaru. What to drive.” with an underline beneath it, and below that: “Offer Ends November 4th.”"
